about.description:
Cloud Data Loss Prevention (DLP) API provides methods for detection, risk analysis, and de-identification of privacy-sensitive fragments in text, images, and Google Cloud Platform storage repositories.
See the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/dlp/latest/index.html#quick-start).
about.summary: Cloud Data Loss Prevention (DLP) API client library

name: google-cloud-dlp
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "google-cloud-dlp" %}
{% set version = "0.14.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "0b9eeb0dabe150bfb9862b84608db4194f78d48d52fc47d856518cc8effc69d5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip >=18.1
  run:
    - python
    - google-api-core-grpc >=1.14.0,<2.0.0dev
    - enum34

test:
  imports:
    - grpc
    - google.cloud.dlp
    - google.cloud.dlp_v2

about:
  home: https://github.com/googleapis/python-dlp
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Cloud Data Loss Prevention (DLP) API client library'
  description: Cloud Data Loss Prevention (DLP) API provides methods for detection, risk analysis, and
    de-identification of privacy-sensitive fragments in text, images, and Google Cloud Platform storage
    repositories.

    See the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/dlp/latest/index.html#quick-start).

  doc_url: https://googleapis.dev/python/dlp/latest/index.html
  dev_url: https://github.com/googleapis/python-dlp

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - parthea
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.1
